Next, the program uses the `SEEK_SET` and `READ_FULL` ioctl commands to read the boot sector of the disk into a buffer. It then loops through the sectors of the disk, using the `SEEK_SET` and `WRITE_FULL` ioctl commands to write the empty boot sector to each sector.

Finally, the program prints a message indicating that the boot sector has been replaced with an empty file and exits.

